DataElement.preferredDefinition: Methodology that testts integrity in experiments by isolating variables as dictated by the scientific method in order to make a conclusion about such variables. Concepts.definition: Methodology that tests integrity in experiments by isolating variables as dictated by the scientific method in order to make a conclusion about such variables. In a controlled experiment, two virtually identical experiments are conducted, but the factor being tested is varied in only one of them. This serves to isolate any causal phenomena.
A functional unit of heredity which occupies a specific position on a particular chromosome and serves as the template for a product that contributes to a phenotype or a biological function.
